<br>
2) Once they do the follow up patch to make pets actually summon at the highest level like they are supposed to, there isn't a downside to this patch.<br>
<br>
Q: Will it make a soloing Mage stronger?<br>
A: No.  A soloing Mage would often continue to resummon their pet after each fight until they got the highest level pet anyway.<br>
<br>
Q: Will it help Mages get groups?<br>
A: If all players understand the relevance of this patch, then the answer is likely Yes.<br>
<br>
A Mages power which has always been largly based on their pet.  However, the damage potential has been inconsistant due to the inability to tell the level of the pet until it engages in combat.  Even then, the mage had to parse the pets battle spam from everyone elses in order see what the pet was hitting for.  Very tedious at best.<br>
<br>
Now Mages will be able to rely on a consistant level of performance from each tier of pet spells, which not only makes them more of a known factor to themselves, but also to groups.<br>
<br>
